Olympique Lyonnais’ (OL) shares fell yesterday after the French soccer club’s defeat to Bayern Munich in the Champions League semi-final. Lyon’s shares, which had risen at the start of the week after Lyon beat Manchester City in the quarterfinal, were down by 4.7% by 0728 GMT. Bayern Munich powered into the Champions League final, where they will face Paris St Germain, as two goals from Serge Gnabry led them to an emphatic 3-0 win over Lyon on Wednesday.